Five-month-old Sonit Awal was asleep upstairs in the family home when the quake struck . 
  He was saved from death by a cupboard that fell on top of him protecting him from the rubble . 
  Mother Rasmila Awal said she could hear her baby crying from the wreckage . 
  Sonit was trapped under rubble for 22 hours before he was found by rescue workers . 
  Mother has spoken of her 'overwhelming joy' that he is alive . 
 